## Inspo meme
The changes I made to the original meme include:

Changing the text color from white to red
Keeping the centered and bold text style

The reason for these changes is:

Red is more eye-catching than white, making the text stand out more and improving the overall visual impact of the meme.

## My meme

library(magick)

meme <- image_read("https://www.meme-arsenal.com/memes/2851200.jpg")
meme <- meme %>%
  image_annotate(
    size = 40,
    color = "red",
    gravity = "north",
    weight = 700
  ) %>%
  image_annotate(
    size = 40,
    color = "red",
    gravity = "south", 
    weight = 700
  )

image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

frame1 <- image_annotate(meme, "1", gravity = "center", size = 50)
frame2 <- image_annotate(meme, "2", gravity = "center", size = 50)
frame3 <- image_annotate(meme, "3", gravity = "center", size = 50)
frame4 <- image_annotate(meme, "4", gravity = "center", size = 50)

animation <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

animation <- image_animate(animation, fps = 1)


image_write(animation, "my_animated_meme.gif")
Changing the text color from white to red
Keeping the centered and bold text style

The reason is:

Red is more eye-catching than white, making the text stand out more and improving the overall visual impact of the meme.

